-- Hungary Attracts $1.2 Billion in Foreign Investment in 2011
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-04-11T12:04:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/hungary-attracts-1-2-billion-in-foreign-investment-in-2011.html
Hungary  attracted 924.3 million
euros ($1.2 billion) in foreign direct investments in 2011,
which will create 5,736 jobs, the  Hungarian Investment and Trade
Agency  said.  The agency last year held talks about more than 5 billion
euros of investment projects, whose completion would add about
18,000  jobs , it said in an e-mailed statement today.  Most companies considering investment in Hungary come from
the U.S.,  Germany  and Asia, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
